ActCriminal Code
SubjectRegulations Amending the Regulations Establishing a List of Entities
PrecisRegulations Amending the REGULATIONS ESTABLISHING A LIST OF ENTITIES in order to (1) replace the name of the existing entity, “Al Qaida in Iraq (AQI)”, with “Islamic State (IS)”, and add the following new aliases to the existing list of entities: “Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant, ISIL, Islamic State of Iraq and Syria, Islamic State of Iraq and al-Sham, ISIS, Al-Dawla Al-Islamiya fi al-Iraq wa al-Sham”; (2) add “Al Qaida in Iraq” as an alias of Islamic State; and (3) remove “The Organization Base of Jihad/Country of the Two Rivers” from the list of existing aliases of Al Qaida in Iraq in the French version of the Regulations.
RegistrationRegistration: SOR/ 2014-0211 Publication Date: 2014-10-08
